#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:233
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:235
msgid ""
"This plugin **requires Vim 7.0+ built with Python 3.10+ support**. It needs "
"Python 3.10 to be able to run _Black_ inside the Vim process which is much "
"faster than calling an external command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:239
msgid "`vim-plug`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:241
msgid "To install with [vim-plug](https://github.com/junegunn/vim-plug):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:243
msgid ""
"_Black_'s `stable` branch tracks official version updates, and can be used "
"to simply follow the most recent stable version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:246
msgid "Plug 'psf/black', { 'branch': 'stable' }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:250
msgid ""
"Another option which is a bit more explicit and offers more control is to "
"use `vim-plug`'s `tag` option with a shell wildcard. This will resolve to "
"the latest tag which matches the given pattern."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:254
msgid ""
"The following matches all stable versions (see the [Release Process](../"
"contributing/release_process.md) section for documentation of version scheme "
"used by Black):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:258
msgid "Plug 'psf/black', { 'tag': '*.*.*' }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:262
msgid ""
"and the following demonstrates pinning to a specific year's stable style "
"(2026 in this case):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:265
msgid "Plug 'psf/black', { 'tag': '26.*.*' }\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:269
msgid "Vundle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:271
msgid "or with [Vundle](https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:273
msgid "Plugin 'psf/black'\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:277
msgid "and execute the following in a terminal:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:279
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/.vim/bundle/black\n"
"$ git checkout origin/stable -b stable\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:284
msgid "Arch Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:286
msgid ""
"On Arch Linux, the plugin is shipped with the [`python-black`](https://"
