#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:306
msgid "Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:308
msgid ""
"On first run, the plugin creates its own virtualenv using the right Python "
"version and automatically installs _Black_. You can upgrade it later by "
"calling `:BlackUpgrade` and restarting Vim."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:312
msgid ""
"If you need to do anything special to make your virtualenv work and install "
"_Black_ (for example you want to run a version from main), create a "
"virtualenv manually and point `g:black_virtualenv` to it. The plugin will "
"use it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:316
msgid ""
"If you would prefer to use the system installation of _Black_ rather than a "
"virtualenv, then add this to your vimrc:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:319
msgid "let g:black_use_virtualenv = 0\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:323
msgid ""
"Note that the `:BlackUpgrade` command is only usable and useful with a "
"virtualenv, so when the virtualenv is not in use, `:BlackUpgrade` is "
"disabled. If you need to upgrade the system installation of _Black_, then "
"use your system package manager or pip-- whatever tool you used to install "
"_Black_ originally."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:328
msgid ""
"To run _Black_ on save, add the following lines to `.vimrc` or `init.vim`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:330
msgid ""
"augroup black_on_save\n"
"  autocmd!\n"
"  autocmd BufWritePre *.py Black\n"
"augroup end\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:337
msgid "To run _Black_ on a key press (e.g. F9 below), add this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:339
msgid "nnoremap <F9> :Black<CR>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:343 ../../../integrations/editors.md:391
msgid "With ALE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../integrations/editors.md:345
msgid "Install [`ale`](https://github.com/dense-analysis/ale)"
